descript.abstract: Mathematically generated grid representing USGS 7 1/2 Minute Quadrangle Map outlines. Quadrangle names and standard identifiers are included with the data set.
descript.purpose: To provide a standard framework for 1:24,000 scale basemap development and ARC/INFO data libraries.

theme.themekey: USGS Map Index, 24K Index, Quadrangle Index, location

dataqual.logic: Data are topolocially correct using ARC/INFO 7.0.3. All polygons are closed and lines intersect where intended.
dataqual.complete: Data are complete for the state of Minnesota

procstep.procdesc: Attribute Lineage for source table INDX_Q024KPY4.DBF: Attributes for Minnesota Quad ID codes and USGS Quadrangle name were then assigned by transferring attributes from an existing file of coordinates maintained at LMIC. The source attributes were tied to the lower left corner of each quad. By generating a point coverage from these coordinates and shifting the point positions to the northwest, label points for this coverage were effectively created. Several specialized attribute fields were dropped from the source polygon attribute table (.PAT) during the Core Database restructuring effort in March of 1996.

attr.attrdef: Minnesota Quad Numbering System ID. Range of all values is 11 to 9926
Contains Q100 Identifier of the 1:100,000 scale quadrangle sheet that the 1:24K quad falls within

edom.edomvd: Quad identifiers follow a row-column format. Values are not continuous.
